      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Rebuilding Alliance demonstrates a strong commitment to direct service delivery. Their <cite id=\"10\">90.3% independent board</cite> ensures objective oversight of operations. The organization's ability to maintain <cite id=\"5\">100.0% program efficiency</cite> while operating in high-conflict zones like Gaza is a significant operational achievement. Furthermore, they have <cite id=\"11\">documented a clear theory of change</cite> that links their advocacy work with tangible protections for Palestinian families."
      ],
      "summary": "Rebuilding Alliance is a dedicated non-profit organization focused on securing equal rights and providing essential humanitarian aid to Palestinian families. Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2003</cite>, the organization operates through a dual-track model that combines <cite id=\"2\">advocacy and legal support</cite> with direct emergency relief. Their work is centered in the <cite id=\"3\">Gaza Strip, West Bank, and Jerusalem</cite>, where they help families maintain their land and homes. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"4\">$825,817 in total revenue</cite>, which was primarily driven by contributions. Despite its modest size, the charity maintains a <cite id=\"5\">90.3% program expense ratio</cite>, ensuring that every dollar of public donation is directed toward its core missions. Key initiatives include a <cite id=\"6\">Hot Meals Program</cite> and the distribution of food parcels to vulnerable families. The organization also facilitates <cite id=\"7\">Leadership Learning Missions</cite> to educate policymakers about the situation on the ground. By focusing on both immediate survival and long-term rights, Rebuilding Alliance serves as a critical bridge between humanitarian need and systemic change for Palestinian communities.",
